2026-04-16 12:17:08 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Control Input Cable (+) 6 low/return connection to Control Module 6', 'Control Module 6 input terminal for the low/return line'] hypothesis_explanation='The observation step found a definitive wiring defect: the return (low/0V) side of the Control Input Cable (+) 6 is floating and not actually connected to the internal low/return terminal of Control Module 6. In this series architecture, each control module passes both the high and low conductors forward. An open in either conductor anywhere in the chain will interrupt current to all downstream loads and indicators. A floating low conductor at CM6 therefore breaks the series loop to modules 6, 7, 8, and the load, preventing the lamp and the last three switch indicators from ever being energized. Depending on how the return path is routed, this open can also prevent earlier module indicators from lighting consistently, matching the symptom that no control-module LEDs are present even though the PSU LED is on. Repairing or correctly terminating this low/return connection at Control Module 6 should restore continuity of the circuit and allow current to flow when all switches are ON, enabling the lamp and indicators to operate.'
