2026-04-16 12:17:32 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Control Module 6 switch indicator LED branch (missing LED and/or its series resistor)'] hypothesis_explanation='Control Module 6’s internal inspection shows that its red switch-indicator LED and its series resistor, which form the only intentional load between the 12 V and 0 V rails inside that cube, are physically missing. In this system the LED+resistor branch is required to complete the internal connection between the module’s high and low lines when the switch is ON. With that branch absent, Control Module 6 behaves as an open circuit even when its switch is closed: upstream modules and indicators can still see correct polarity at their connectors (as observed), but no current can flow through CM6 to the downstream modules and load, so the lamp never energizes. Replacing/restoring the LED-resistor indicator branch in Control Module 6 should re-establish continuity and allow current to reach the load when all switches are ON.'
