2026-04-16 12:17:54 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Load module internal wiring from +12V input to series diode cathode and to both lamp positive terminals'] hypothesis_explanation='Visual inspection showed that inside the Load Module the protection diode’s anode is tied to the +12V input but its cathode is left unconnected, and both the main lamp and indicator lamp have only their negative terminals connected (to the 0V input) with no positive connection. This means there is an open circuit on the high side of the load: no current can reach either lamp regardless of upstream module status. The fault is therefore a missing/incorrect internal connection from the +12V input to the diode cathode and onward to the positive terminals of both lamps. Restoring proper wiring from the Load Input (+) to the diode and lamp positives should complete the circuit and allow the lamp to operate when all switches are ON.'
